content.rendered:
You need to know the current WEATHER GUARD® PRCA 2022 World Standings (All-Around) – in accordance with the money won during the regular season, the Justin Boots Playoffs and Championships, and for many bull riders, the PRCA Xtreme Bulls Tour.

Watch NFR 2023 Live Online - SUBSCRIBE HERE

NFR 2023 Streaming info
Streaming
The Cowboy Channel (real-time) Watch Here
RFD-TV (real-time) Watch Here
Cowboy Channel Plus (International) Watch Here

 

As the 2022 regular season nears the conclusion, it seems easier to estimate who the winners will be. Still, anything can happen with the looks of things as top rodeo professionals compete for the top prize at the 2022 All-Around World Standing.

Here is an insight for the 2022 All-Around World Standings.

Defending champion Stetson Wright sits in a familiar spot to clinch this year All-Around title that he won last year. He is the favorite to emerge victorious following the stunning and marvelous streak that helped him qualify for the Bull Riding. This automatically means he will feature for the NFR in Saddle Bronc Riding.

The second place is Paden Bray, and he will need all the luck in the world to catchup against the reigning 2020 All-Around champion by winning big in NFR Tie-Down Roping.

The 2-time world champion (2018-2019) Clay Smith, a team roper, is expected to put up an intense fight for the 2022 All-Round championship, thus making the competition a must-watch one as the 2022 All-Around Championship comes to an end.
